name: 阿福鱼圆肉脞面 (Ah Hock fish ball mined meat noodle)

reviews.text:
Happen to be running some errands nearby Frontier  building and decided to pop by for late breakfast. Chanced upon this stall inside the food court that sells fishball noodle with a queue. There were about 5 pax ahead of me when i was there. Apart from fishball noodle, they also sells laksa.

The noodle was nicely cooked, texture of the noodle was springy. The sauce was well balanced and goes really well. My bowl of noodle came with sliced fishcake,fishball,  liver, minced pork and fried wanton.

Overall, it an above average bowl of fishball noodle for me and would definitely recommend if you are nearby Frontier. Only downside if you ask me would be the portion of the noodle is quite little.

stall located within foodcourt of an industrial building. at $4.50 is very value for money as uncle is generous with ingredients. also very friendly. my top choice for fishball noodles around the vicinity. fried kway teow is also available though I haven't had the chance to try. lots of parking options available as there's also a big carpark next to the building.
Fishball Noodles cooked by an old uncle, but it is tasty and texture is QQ springy. Well cooked and nicely presented. Give me a bonus prawn too! Value for money. Must try!

Kway teow soup is tasty and traditional. Price reasonable,  please support him, I see he so old already still want to cook traditional  kway teow soup for us. But really nice so I recommend if you nearby please support.  I Tried mee pok also very nice, chilli is nice too.
